---

I see the golden sun descending
Like a ship out of the sea,
And the shadows creeping on the meadows,
The night begins to be.

The stars in the skies glitter over me,
And the moon is a silvery sheen,
The flowers close their petals soft,
As the darkness draws over the green.

- Robert Southey
